PERTH (miningweekly.com) – Junior Blackstone Minerals has announced plans to raise more than A$20-million through a share placement and share purchase plan (SPP) to fund ongoing work at the Ta Khoa nickel/platinum group metals project, in northern Vietnam. The company said on Monday that it had received firm commitments from sophisticated, professional and institutional investors for the placement of more than 42.4-million shares, at a price of 42c each, to raise an initial A$17.8-million. The share placement will be conducted under the company’s existing capacity, and will not require shareholder approval. In addition, Blackstone will also undertake an SPP to raise a further A$3-million, allowing shareholders to subscribe for up to A$30 000 of additional shares in the company. “We are excited to welcome new long term institutional investors to our register and the opportunity to raise A$21-million for Blackstone to support the ongoing exploration, resource drilling and future studies at the Ta Khoa project,” said MD Scott Williamson.